metadata.name: Solitude #190
metadata.description:
Solitude is a study of negative space, contrast and void; made with 6 different particle systems. It's about the loneliness, energy dependency of our species and our interest towards monumental constructions.

------

In 3541, when Solitude was far from its former glory, the high council was assembling; it's now time to find a new way to live. It has been centuries since our people started to harness the power of the stars, but they used every last bit of power to serve as a mass effort to bring people together and strengthen solidarity. But now just a few remain.. With a shortage of manpower and energy, everything decayed so quickly. Now this isolated civilization is built upon the dying stars and waiting for the eternal void. 

It's time for the high council to assemble for one last time to decide what to do next…

------

The first 5 collectors at the highest tier(60 xtz) will receive an airdrop of an additional edition minted by us and also will have a guaranteed reserve spot for our next collection.

In live mode, press ‘s’ to save as .png (4000 x 7111 px) - You can check the console to confirm if the render is finished.

Please beware there are some minor differences  -caused by different pixel densities- between the saved .png and work on the site.

It can take up to a minute to render or longer in low-performance computers. Enjoy the process!

Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, August 2022
@distcollective

metadata.name: Bustling Bright #12
metadata.description:
'Bustling Bright' is a generative drawing on the conpect of the nature of flowers, light, and ground, in an planer and abstract art style. I explore different geometric layouts to mimic variants of plants structures in the nature environment of my garden, full of youth and vitality. The representation of ground is aggregated by group of polygons, filled with smooth and chaotic textures.

This work is also an exploration of generative art in its deterministic structures and stochastic variants. I try to use minimal factors to construct a rich, varied and meaningful results. The constrints and combinations between parameters/factors are deterministic parts of the generative art and the emergence of variety in the complex generation process is its stochastic and unpredictable soul. The deterministic structure provides a stable state of the generative process, but the stochastic parts give the most interesting and unique feelings of the artwork. So what is a generative artwortk? In my opinion, the genrative artwork is not about any one piece of generated result. The Generative artwork is about the total generative space, which represents its all structures and varieties. The creation process of a generative art is not about the author, but also with all its collectors in minting. Because this is a samling process of the generative space, and it is the only way for our human to feel and understand this high dimensional generative space.

I hope you like this work and enjoy the whole nature in its beauty.

Variables:
- 7 strucure pattern
- 17 color palette
- 2 layout

Please be patient with drawing process.

metadata.name: The Magic of Color and Light #15
metadata.description:
As Alice continued to explore the world of generative art, she became more and more interested in the ways that color and light could be used to enhance her designs. She had always been drawn to the vibrant, lively energy of colorful compositions, and she decided to see what she could create using the rough.js library to add colorful shadows to her rectangles.

Alice began by defining a few simple parameters for her design, such as the size and position of the rectangles and the intensity and hue of the shadows. She then spent hours playing with different combinations of colors and shadow effects, trying to find the perfect balance between vibrancy and harmony.

As she worked, Alice found herself getting lost in the process, completely absorbed in the world of generative art. She loved the way the rectangles seemed to come to life on the screen, their shadows shifting and changing as she played with the parameters.

Eventually, after much experimentation and creativity, Alice hit upon a beautiful and dynamic composition that she felt was truly special. She saved her work and sat back to admire it, feeling a sense of pride and accomplishment wash over her.

And so, with her passion for art and color driving her forward, Alice had created yet another stunning piece of generative art, using the rough.js library to bring her vision to life.

In live mode Press "s" to save image (2200 x 3030).

+---+
The Magic of Color and Light by __Reiji_c
+---+
